title: Time Domain vs Frequency Domain | Frequency–Phase Math #tutorial #cse #computerscience #education
description:
In this video, we cover the most important signal math concepts used in Data Communication / Signals: Frequency, Phase, Time Domain, and Frequency Domain. You will also learn how these concepts connect in numericals and exam problems.

✅ Topics covered:

Frequency (f) and Period (T) relationship

f = 1/T, T = 1/f

Phase (φ) and phase shift

Understanding 0°, 90°, 180° phase shift

How phase indicates the starting position of a waveform

Time Domain representation

Signal shown as amplitude vs time

How to interpret waveform changes over time

Frequency Domain representation

Signal shown as amplitude vs frequency

Why real signals are often composite (multiple frequencies)

Key idea: how a signal in time domain can be understood as a combination of frequency components in frequency domain

🧮 Math examples included (step-by-step):

Converting frequency ↔ period

Identifying phase shift effects on waveform timing

Understanding frequency components in composite signals

description:

What is Frequency (f) and what it means in a signal

Unit of frequency: Hertz (Hz), kHz, MHz, GHz

Relationship between Frequency and Period

f = 1 / T

T = 1 / f

How to convert:

Hz ↔ kHz ↔ MHz

seconds ↔ milliseconds ↔ microseconds
